    <abstract>Compiled by Fang Xuanling 房玄齡 (578–648) in 646–648. Tang Taizong composed four
        passages in it and therefore the Jinshu was designated “imperially compiled.” The Jinshu has
        been faulted for reflecting early Tang court politics rather than the realities of the Jin
        dynasty.” [Wilkinson 2015, 730]</abstract>
